    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vessels supported by two, three or four small legs, often refers particularly to Middle American archaeological objects and also the European Beaker culture of the Neolithic and Early Bronze Age.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
